    "summary": " Rome is a city rich in history and culture. On day one, you will visit the Park of the Aqueducts where you can learn about the ancient Roman engineering that brought water to the city. You will also explore Sapienza University of Rome which is one of Europe's oldest universities. MATREM Bakery offers traditional Italian baked goods and Mamma Pizza serves up delicious pizzas with a variety of toppings. Casina delle civette is an elegant restaurant that serves Mediterranean cuisine, while Villa Blanc is known for its exquisite desserts. Associazione Culturale Islamicaمسجد الهدى is a mosque in Rome where you can learn about the Muslim faith and its history. 180grammi Asporto e Delivery (Centocelle) offers fresh, local produce that has been delivered within an hour of being harvested. On day two, you will visit the Capitoline Museums which house ancient Roman artifacts such as statues and coins. The Roman Forum is a must-see attraction where you can walk among the ruins of this once bustling marketplace. Mamertine Prison was used to hold prisoners before they were executed in the nearby Monument to Victor Emmanuel II. Le Domus Romane di Palazzo Valentini is an archaeological site that showcases the remains of Roman villas, while Mercati di Traiano Museo dei Fori Imperiali displays artifacts from ancient Rome's marketplace. Sacripant Art Gallery features contemporary artwork by local artists, and Basilica Papale di Santa Maria Maggiore is a beautiful church with stunning frescoes and sculptures. On day three, you will visit Fungo dell'Eur which is an artificial hill that was created for the 1942 World's Fair in Rome. Giardino delle Cascate is a botanical garden that showcases various plants from around the world, while Parco EUR Fermi offers walking trails and picnic areas for visitors to enjoy. Parco del Lago dell'EUR has a lake where you can rent boats or simply relax in nature. Sushi Love serves up fresh sushi rolls with a variety of ingredients, while Gustus Pizza Napoletana offers traditional Neapolitan pizza that is made using only the finest ingredients. On day four, you will visit Chiesa del Gesù which is a church known for its Baroque architecture and artwork by some of Italy's most famous painters such as Caravaggio and Annibale Carracci. Basilica of Saint Mary of Minerva is another must-see attraction that houses the remains of Saint Catherine of Siena, while Pantheon is a marvel of ancient Roman engineering that still stands today. Chiesa di Sant'Ignazio di Loyola is a church known for its stunning frescoes and sculptures by some of Italy's most famous artists such as Gian Lorenzo Bernini. Piazza di Spagna is an elegant square where you can visit the Spanish Steps, while Trevi Fountain is one of Rome's most iconic landmarks that attracts tourists from all over the world who come to toss their coins into its waters for good luck. Galleria Doria Pamphilj showcases artwork by some of Italy's most famous artists such as Raphael and Titian, while Palazzo Bonaparte is a historic building that was once home to Napoleon Bonaparte during his time in Rome."
